I'm trying to write a program that adds random numbers 0-1000 to a text file: :The user chooses the file name and the number of random numbers. As of now, the program only saves the last random number to the text filepublic static void main(String[] args) throws FileNotFoundException, UnsupportedEncodingException {    Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);    System.out.println("Enter a filename:");    String filename = scan.nextLine();    System.out.println("Enter a positive Integer:");    int number = scan.nextInt();    for (int i=0; i<number;i++){        Random rand= new Random();        int random = rand.nextInt(1001);        PrintWriter writer = new PrintWriter (filename, "UTF-8");        writer.println(random);        writer.close();         System.out.println(random);    }    }
